{"type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Slot Components (Headless-style)\n      Children use <DrawerTitle>, <DrawerBody>, <DrawerBottomPanel> to declare content that renders into the correct physical location via React context portals.\n      <Drawer pagination={pagination}>\n  <DrawerPage id=\"details\">\n    <DrawerTitle>Transaction Details</DrawerTitle>\n    <TransactionSummary />\n    <DrawerBottomPanel>\n      <Button onClick={() => open('edit')}>Edit</Button>\n    </DrawerBottomPanel>\n  </DrawerPage>\n\n  <DrawerPage id=\"edit\">\n    <DrawerTitle>Edit Transaction</DrawerTitle>\n    <EditForm />  {/* can use DrawerBottomPanel inside */}\n  </DrawerPage>\n</Drawer>\n      \n        Pros\n          Most flexible — slot components work at any nesting depth\n          Fully co-located: page content + its chrome live together\n          Sub-components (EditForm) can inject bottomPanel without prop drilling\n          Familiar pattern (Radix, Headless UI)\n        \n        Cons\n          More internal complexity (context-based portals)\n          Need to handle multiple DrawerTitle/DrawerBottomPanel conflicts\n          Timing: portals must sync with page transitions","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775598379059}
